  <span id="freeText8802569620089055252" style="display:none">I suspect that with a re-read of this book I'd probably give it a 5-star rating. I went into this book not really knowing what to expect, I was very intrigued by the title.<br /><br />This was a strangely compelling book,though it took a while for me to get into it.It's a story full of magical realism, which I read that someone described as a dream/nightmare. A very fitting description. <br />I had no idea who the narrators were half the time but I did enjoy it a lot. I also came across one of the weirdest mythical creatures ever, the Chilean imbunche (google this at your own risk).<br /><br />I would also advise the reader to not read this book while eating. There are some truly candid and disturbing descriptions throughout the book.</span>
